    "summary": "I am interested in structure detection and analysis in the cosmic web and galactic archeology domains. I am especially interested in applying Machine Learning methodologies to detect and extract structure within point cloud data sets including 3D cosmological N-body simulations, and astrometric data from the Gaia mission. My recent work involved looking at simulated cosmic filaments as well as studying the properties of stellar streams in the halo of the Milky Way.\n\nMy 4+  years' experience with handling astrophysical data gives me the ability to apply my knowledge in data science positions in industry. \n\nRecent explorations of mine are Beysian variational inference and probabilistic modelling.",
